# Ultimate Discord Intelligence Bot - Project Structure

## Core Architecture

The main entry point is [main.py](mdc:src/ultimate_discord_intelligence_bot/main.py), which orchestrates the CrewAI-based debate analysis system. Configuration is managed through [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) and YAML files in the [config/](mdc:config/) directory.

## Key Directories

- **src/ultimate_discord_intelligence_bot/**: Main application package with agents, tools, and pipeline
- **src/ingest/**: Multi-platform content ingestion (YouTube, Twitch, TikTok, Reddit, etc.)
- **src/analysis/**: Debate analysis, fact-checking, and scoring logic
- **src/memory/**: Vector storage integration with Qdrant
- **src/grounding/**: Context verification and fact-checking backends
- **src/discord/**: Discord bot commands and integrations
- **src/policy/**: Privacy, security, and content policies
- **config/**: YAML configuration files for agents, tasks, and services
- **tests/**: Comprehensive test suite with pytest
- **docs/**: Documentation including [agent_reference.md](mdc:docs/agent_reference.md)

## Project Standards

- **Python 3.10+** with type hints and comprehensive docstrings
- **CrewAI framework** for agent orchestration
- **Qdrant** for vector storage and semantic search
- **Discord.py** for bot functionality
- **pytest** for testing with async support
- **ruff** for linting and formatting (120 char line length)
- **mypy** for type checking with baseline management

## Key Files

- [crew.py](mdc:src/ultimate_discord_intelligence_bot/crew.py): CrewAI crew definition
- [settings.py](mdc:src/ultimate_discord_intelligence_bot/settings.py): Application settings
- [step_result.py](mdc:src/ultimate_discord_intelligence_bot/step_result.py): Standard result format
- [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md): Comprehensive project guidelines and progress tracker
- [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md): System architecture documentation
